        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 3:30PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 330 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Todd Mission, or 8 miles west of Pinehurst, moving northwest at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tomball, Pinehurst, Magnolia, Stagecoach, Todd Mission,
Plantersville, and Dobbin.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
